import Mathlib

open Filter Real Measure Topology

/-!
  We prove that the map T has Lorentz type (4 * c / p) by showing that for any
  function f with finite support, the eLorentz norm of T f is bounded by (4 * c / p)
  times the eLorentz norm of f times the product of the measures of the support
  of f and the target set G.
  This involves decomposing f into its real and imaginary parts, which are non-negative
  functions, and then applying known bounds for such functions.
  We use the linearity properties of T and the fact that T maps strongly
  measurable functions to strongly measurable functions.
